quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  22,6,"That is because indeed Allah is the Truth, and because indeed He gives life to the dead, and because indeed He is Powerful over everything."
  22,7,"And because the Hour is indeed coming—there is no doubt about it—and because indeed Allah resurrects those in the graves."
  22,8,"And of mankind is one who argues about Allah without knowledge or guidance or an illuminating scripture,"
  22,9,"turning aside in contempt, to make<i>(others) </i>stray{1}from the way of Allah; for him in the Earlier<i>(Life) </i>is disgrace, and on the Day of Resurrection We make him taste the punishment of burning:",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Roways read it as: “…to stray from the way of Allah;”
  22,10,"“That is for what your<sup>sg </sup>hands{1}have put forth, and because Allah is not a tyrant unto the servants.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person to 2<sup><small>nd</small></sup> person.
